<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\04_defiance_bay_brackenbury\04_cv_moedred</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>104</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>An animancer scribbles feverishly on a parchment scroll while his free hand dances through the air, counting off unseen objects. His lips move in silent discourse.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>As your shadow falls over his scroll, he looks up at you with mingled perplexity and irritation.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can I help you?" He forces a polite smile.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What are you working on?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Does the name Helig mean anything to you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Just looking around."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Then be quick about it. And don't touch anything. The sanitarium has a lax visitor policy, but I don't."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He left his post recently. I believe he was seeking new opportunities in the Vailian Republics." He leans forward. "The advances they're making in animancy really are quite remarkable. Surely you've heard?" He coughs again. "Perhaps you haven't."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText>Without another word, he resumes his work.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"My area of focus is wichts. More specifically, how to cure them."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred looks up from his scroll. "Yes?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've heard it differently."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Do you know a woman named Rowyna?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I see."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>He slides his spectacles down his nose. "Just what are you insinuating? If this is your idea of a joke, I assure you, it's in very poor taste."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Now, if you'll excuse me, I'm already behind." He waves at the door. "Please show yourself out."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So you didn't sink a blade into his chest and dump him in the catacombs? He'll be relieved to hear it." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Crack your knuckles.] "I insinuate nothing. Subtlety isn't my style."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Never mind. It's not important."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred pales. "How could...?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred gapes at you. "You wouldn't."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I usually do."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Quit wasting my time, animancer."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I would. And I'd enjoy it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Helig is dead. For good." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What are you doing? Cathwin, no!" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred starts. "Helig? He was - is, I mean - a colleague of mine. He was primarily a necromancer, but he was involved in animancy, too. He worked at the sanitarium for several years. I daresay everyone here has heard of him." He clears his throat. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Helig wasn't joking, and neither am I." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText>He sighs and runs a hand over his hair. "...Very well. Yes, I killed him. I killed that beast because nobody else had the spine for it." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He was a madman. Years of perverse experiments - twisting healthy souls, torturing damaged souls - and for what? He flayed the essence from Glanfathan indigents for his amusement." He waves down the hall. "If the public had known half of his deeds, they'd have razed this place to the ground."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>He jabs his finger on the desk. "He used the sanitarium to disguise his own sick proclivities. He brought shame on all of us and put the entire discipline at risk. I regret nothing."

He calms down and sizes you up. "Anyway, now you know the whole grisly story."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I've had enough of these baseless..." Moedred pauses. "Wait. You spoke to Helig?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred nods, taking a deep breath. "Then, if there's nothing else...?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"About Helig..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred smooths his robes. "As I said, he no longer works here." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No. I don't get out of the sanitarium much." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'll be on my way." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Hardly brave, stabbing a man in his sleep." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Helig's alive, in a manner of speaking." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So you killed him to save your own reputation?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Helig lives. In a manner of speaking." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He's talkative for a dead man." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I suppose not. But I heard a different story from Helig, and I intend to get the truth." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I see." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes? What about him?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred frowns. "That's not..." He pauses. "No, I suppose it is possible. That mad hound was steeped in all manner of foul arts." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You say you spoke to him? How?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>"But that's..." Moedred frowns. "If anyone figured out how to do that, it would be him, wouldn't it?" He sighs.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>60</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Helig's soul returned to his corpse through sinister magic. He wants revenge." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>63</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Helig's soul returned to his corpse through sinister magic. He wants revenge." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>64</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No doubt." He spreads his hands wide. "But now you understand why I killed him. Why someone had to."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>65</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Brave enough for my tastes. I heard a rumor he once laid a fifty-man squad to rest on his own." 

"At least I did something." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>66</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred snorts. "The reputation of the whole discipline, rather. You realize there are groups in this city looking for an excuse to have us all hanged?"

He shakes his head. "I won't see the knowledge we've worked so hard for lost because of one man's madness."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>69</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If he's sent you, I only hope I can convince you to return and slay him once and for all." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>73</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'll finish him." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>74</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'll consider it." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>75</ID>
      <DefaultText>"He has something I need." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>76</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Perhaps. I'll be going." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>77</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred nods, relieved. "Good. I'm glad someone finally will." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>78</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I must return to my work. I wish you well." Moedred turns back to his papers.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>79</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You'd consider a deal with that monster?" He puts his head in his hands. "If what I've told you hasn't swayed you, I doubt anything will."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>80</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Consider also the kind of man he is and the kind of things he's capable of. Don't trust him."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>81</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred lets out a long breath. "Then I can rest easy. You've done a great service for animancy, for the sanitarium... and for me. Thank you." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>83</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Glad to be of help. Farewell." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>87</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Of course. Take your time." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>88</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Wait!" Moedred shoots you a baleful look. "There's no need for that." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>89</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I confess it. I killed that beast because nobody else had the spine for it." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>90</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Never mind." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>92</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Helig said you stole a grimoire from him." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>93</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred's brow furrows. "His grimoire? What's that madman been telling you?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>94</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm not in the mood for games, Moedred. Hand it over." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>95</ID>
      <DefaultText>[Give him the key.] "He said you kept it in that trunk over there." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>96</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If you don't have it, where is it?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>97</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred spreads his hands. "I'm not a wizard, and I want nothing to do with his detestable research. What use would I have for it?" </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>98</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred takes the key with a trembling hand, his eyes darting to the trunk behind you. 

"You've been misled. There's no grimoire here, and Helig never intended you to find one."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>103</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If I know Helig, this is his idea of a joke. Probably not one you or I would appreciate."

"If anything I've told you about him has sunk in, I beg you, return to the catacombs and slay him once and for all. That foul man will cause misery and pain as long as he's around."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>104</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That wretched thing has an insatiable hunger for blood." He shudders. "Thank you for denying him."

"I hope I can convince you now to return and slay him once and for all."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>108</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't know what he's promised you, but he's already lied to you about the grimoire. I don't have it."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>109</ID>
      <DefaultText>"If what I've told you about that evil, deceitful man hasn't swayed you, I don't know what else to say." He turns back to his papers. "Trust him at your own peril."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>110</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Are you the animancer who's been buying relics from Imatl?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>111</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Who? I don't have time to barter with adventurers, if that's what this is about."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>112</ID>
      <DefaultText>"It started with a heavy dose of svef..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>113</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Does it matter? He's returned to power and he wants revenge."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>114</ID>
      <DefaultText>Moedred folds his arms. "Oh, very funny. Laugh while you can, because if that vile man has cheated death, there's no end to the suffering he'll cause."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>115</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What's a wicht?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>116</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why do you study wichts?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>117</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I see."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>118</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A Hollowborn who received a transplanted animal soul during infancy. One of animancy's early efforts to cure the Legacy, if not a successful one."

He removes his spectacles and wipes his brow. "They show signs of developmental abnormalities throughout their childhood, but when they reach adolescence, they become aggressive. Feral. But... still victims in need of care."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>120</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Good." He looks eager to return to his work.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>121</ID>
      <DefaultText>He huffs. "What kind of question is that? Just think of all the families that could be healed, the lives that could be restored. What could be more important?" His face has reddened, and he turns away from you for a moment.

He shakes his head. "Animancy has an answer here. I know it. It's simply a matter of working it out."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>122</ID>
      <DefaultText>"The Head Warden must be told what's going on down here!"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>123</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Has anything unusual been happening around here?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>124</ID>
      <DefaultText>"You must be joking. This is the sanitarium - NOTHING is usual down here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>125</ID>
      <DefaultText>He pauses. "Although, now that I think of it, the patients seem more agitated lately. But, they're Caedman Azo's responsibility, not mine."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>126</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I'm looking for an expert on Awakenings."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>127</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I hear that Vailian woman studies them. You should go talk to her instead."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>128</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Transplanting animal souls into children seems like an odd solution."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>129</ID>
      <DefaultText>"We... animancers were trying to do something about the crisis. Better than letting it swallow a generation of children."

He stares at a fixed point on the far wall. "And despite the controversy, it only went so far because, at first, it seemed to work. People called it 'the Salvation.' Children that had never been responsive to any kind of stimuli suddenly seemed aware of their surroundings. Of their families."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>130</ID>
      <DefaultText>He takes a slow breath. "The complications don't begin until puberty. But that's when the incompatibilities between body and soul take shape. Children become violent. Ravenous.

"But we paid dearly for our mistake, I promise you. Angry mobs hunted down animancers and burned down their homes - with them still inside, often as not."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>131</ID>
      <DefaultText>"People took to calling it 'the Cruel Salvation,' and many still loathe us for it. But we wanted to stop the Legacy as much as anyone. The public begged for our help, and we did the best we could. I still don't know if that absolves us."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>132</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Grieving Mother recoils. "A grotesque manipulation... a desperate solution for a desperate problem. And the parents were heartbroken, betrayed..." 

She closes her eyes and seems to recede from you for a moment. "But it was important to try something, was it not? To bring hope, even for a little while..." She falls silent.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>133</ID>
      <DefaultText>The Grieving Mother reaches out, as if to put a hand on Moedred's cheek. "Such pain, Watcher... and such determination..."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>135</ID>
      <DefaultText>He sighs and runs a hand over his hair. "I can hardly be surprised that you figured this out. Yes, I killed him. I killed that beast because nobody else had the spine for it." </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>137</ID>
      <DefaultText>He sighs and runs a hand over his hair. "...Very well. Yes, I killed him. I killed that beast because nobody else had the spine for it." He looks at you more closely. "But doesn't your own order prize such ruthlessness?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
</StringTableFile>